    dc:date "2020" ;
    dc:title "On Sahastata (Araneae: Filistatidae): complementary description of the generotype and two new species from Oman and Morocco" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4400428>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4400442>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4400472>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4400470>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4400452>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4400434> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4400428>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Sahastata spp., living specimens.A–B S. nigra (Simon, 1897) from Jebel Shams, Oman, male (A) and female (B); C–D S. wesolowskae sp. nov. from Salalah, Oman, male holotype (C) and female (D); S. wunderlichi sp. nov. from Zag, Morocco, male (E) and female (F). Scale bars: 10 mm (except E, 5 mm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4400428/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4400442>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Sahastata nigra (Simon, 1897), male from Oman, Ad Dakhliyah, Al Hamra, Jebel Shams mountains (MACN-Ar 39464). A Clypeus, anterior; B Left leg I, proclaw, prolateral; C Right leg II (mirrored), proclaw, prolateral; D Epiandrium, ventral; E Spinnerets, ventral. Scale bars: 200 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4400442/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4400472>
    dc:description "FIGURE 19. Sahastata wunderlichi sp. nov., male paratype from Zag, Morocco (MACN-Ar 39465). A Clypeus, anterior; B Left leg I, proclaw, retrolateral; C Left leg II, proclaw, prolateral. Scale bars: 100 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4400472/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4400470>
    dc:description "FIGURE 18. Sahastata wunderlichi sp. nov., male paratype from Zag, Morocco (MACN-Ar 39465). A Habitus, dorsal; B Carapace, dorsal; C Habitus, lateral; D Habitus, ventral; E Spinnerets, ventral; F Right femur I, retrolateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm except for E, 200 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4400470/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4400452>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Sahastata nigra (Simon, 1897), female from Jebel Shams mountains, Oman (MACN-Ar 38368). A Left calamistrum, dorsal, arrow to row with unmodified setae; B Right calamistrum, subdorsal; C Spinnerets, ventral; D Left ALS, ventral, arrows to major ampullate gland spigots; E PMS, ventral; F Carapace, dorsal. Scale bars: 100 µm except for F, 1 mm.Abbreviations: BS—broadened setae; PC—paracribellar gland spigots; US—unmodified setae." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4400452/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4400434>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Distribution map of Sahastata. Small dots are unidentified specimens or literature records of dubious specific identity." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4400434/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

